 India: Peiping has again raised with New Delhi the subject of a civil air agreement. At present, Burma is the only nonbloc Asian nation with which Communist China has an air agreement. New Delhi has just signed an air agreement with the USSR and may accede to Peiping's request. (Page 1)\n\nUSSR - Latin America: The highest ranking delegations from the USSR and the Eastern European satellites to visit Latin America in recent years will attend the inauguration of Argentine President-elect Frondizi on 1 May. The Soviet delegation will include First Deputy Foreign Minister Kuznetsov, who will also visit Mexico briefly. The bloc representation will include Rumania, Poland, Czechoslovakia, Hungary, and Bulgaria, and will add impetus to the bloc's intensified efforts to increase trade and diplomatic relations with Latin America", "token_count": 135, "token_end_0based": 142, "token_start_0based": 8, "token_text": "i the communist bloc communist china india peiping has again raised with new delhi the subject of a civil air agreement at present burma is the only nonbloc asian nation with which communist china has an air agreement new delhi has just signed an air agreement with the ussr and may accede to peiping's request page 1 ussr latin america the highest ranking delegations from the ussr and the eastern european satellites to visit latin america in recent years will attend the inauguration of argentine president-elect frondizi on 1 may the soviet delegation will include first deputy foreign minister kuznetsov who will also visit mexico briefly the bloc representation will include rumania poland czechoslovakia hungary and bulgaria and will add impetus to the bloc's intensified efforts to increase trade and diplomatic relations with latin america", "unred_source_page": 13}
